main event: Several Air Force personnel observed a group of unidentified objects maneuvering in the sky over Presque Isle Air Force Base, Maine on July 25, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright, circular, and capable of high-speed, erratic maneuvers.,The sighting lasted approximately 40 minutes.,The objects were tracked on radar by the tower controller and the GCI radar station.,The tower controller reported that the objects moved at speeds in excess of 500 knots.,There were no aircraft from Presque Isle Air Force Base or any other known source in the area at the time of the sighting.
witness description: Air Force personnel including 1/Lt Arthur J. Stahl and Airman 1/c John E. Dzierzanowski
